    "id": "membership-renewal"
  }, "Membership renewal"), mdx("p", null, "The coronavirus came at the worst possible time. The moment when memberships were being extended for half a year. It could\u2019ve easily happened that half of the members would\u2019ve suddenly quit, and the club would\u2019ve started to decline. People in our parent organization, Toastmasters International, were also aware of this, so they extended the deadline for paying the membership fee until the end of April. It didn\u2019t quite help. Most clubs, including ours, recorded the departure of members. At the end of April, eleven members left our club. Only ten of us stayed."), mdx("div", {
